      "schema:url": "https://meop.net/groups/usa.html",
      "schema:description": "MEOP (Marine Mammals Exploring the Oceans Pole to Pole) is a consortium of international researchers dedicated to sharing animal-derived data and knowledge about the polar oceans. Collectively, MEOP demonstrates the power and cost-effectiveness of using marine mammals as data-collection platforms that can dramatically improve the ocean-observing system for biological and physical oceanographers.\r\nDeployment sites: Ross Sea, Antarctic Peninsula, Ano Nuevo California state park, Alaska, St Paul (Bering Sea)\r\nSupporting institutions: National Oceanographic Partnership Program, Office of Polar Program, National Science Foundation, and NOAA Antarctic Marine Living Resources Program",
